reviews.review_text: amazing recording these tapers knew where to find the sweet spot!
Charlotte This is the best recording ive heard to date of this show. It was a wonderful nite.

sloppy show esp s2 1st set is pretty good, but honestly s2 is quite sloppy, gasping for air. Yes, a good deal of 84 has that 'junky' kind of delivery and is still great, but this one just isn't as good as many others in the period.
Fine Show This is a fine show from 1984 ,very solid first set. Nice China Rider Highlights second set. Overall well played.

Brent on Rooster Holy shit, whoever screams Brent before the song set the tone, and mustve encouraged Brent to lay it down, cause this is one of the finest Roosters ever played. I almost shat myself when Jerry comes back on his second solo after Bobby, and just obliterates what little was left. Beast mode.

correct better sound then the rest This sound has that being there feel to it. has punch to it.
 I also very much enjoyed this show the day of and many years later.
Spanish Jam I think that little bit of noodling before the Other One can legitimately be called a "Spanish Jam"
CLASSIC 84 DEAD! Always enjoyed this show. 1st is all good, the 2nd set rocking china rider estimated & that black peter!?
